descript.abstract: The dataset contains building footprint outlines for all non-residential buildings with a footprint greater than 2000 sq ft. and all multi-residential buildings with a footprint greater than 2000 sq ft within Waterloo Region. The footprints were digitized from various aerial photography products covering Waterloo Region or were imported from a building footprint dataset supplied by the City of Kitchener
descript.purpose: This dataset was created for use as a reference layer for digital and hardcopy maps and applications. This data should not be used as a measure of building square footage, as the individual polygons only represent the square footage of the footprint at ground level as visible from aerial photography. The building may or may not have multiple floors of varying areas.

dataqual.complete: This dataset contains building footprint polygons for non-residential and multi-residential buildings with a footprint over 2000 square feet. Single residential building footprints are not included. The footprints for Waterloo and Cambridge municipalities were digitized from the 2006 10cm resolution aerial photos. The buildings that were digitized were identified using the MPAC property code data. In cases where the multiple buildings may exist on a property, if the main building matched the criteria then the outlying buildings were digitized as well regardless of square footage. The City of Kitchener footprints were provided to the Region of Waterloo by the City of Kitchener and incorporated into the dataset. The Kitchener footprints seem to have been last updated in February 2007. The building footprints in the Townships of North Dumfries, Wilmot, Wellesley, and Woolwich were digitized with a combination of the 2006 10cm and 2006 30cm aerial photos. The buildings that were digitized were identified using the MPAC property code data. In cases where the multiple buildings may exist on a property, if the main building matched the criteria then the outlying buildings were digitized as well regardless of square footage.

horizpa.horizpar: Horizontal positional accuracy of the footprint polygons was tested by manual comparison with the source media (Aerial Imagery) for all municipalities in the Region of Waterloo

srcinfo.srccontr: The 2003 10cm imagery was used in 2005 to digitize the building footprints in Waterloo and Cambridge.
The building footprints for the City of Kitchener

The RMW_Pt dataset was used to identify buildings that matched the criteria of non-residential or multi-residential and over 2000 sq ft. The RMW_pt dataset contained such information from the MPAC data.

Provided graphic image to digitize building footprints for following areas: Cambridge, Kitchener, Waterloo, Ayr, Bloomingdale, Breslau, Heidelberg, 401/97 Industrial Area, New Dundee, New Hamburg, Baden, St. Clements, Elmira, St. Jacobs, and Wellesley

procstep.procdesc: Took copy of Bldg_Lg dataset that was updated in 2005 using the 2003 10cm imagery and Kitchener building footprints and deleted all building footprints located in Townships of North Dumfries, Wellesley, Wilmot and Woolwich and proceeded to redigitize all non-residential or multi-residential structures > 2000 sq ft. A subset of the RMW_pt dataset was used to identify non-residential and multi-residential structures by way of property code.

Using an updated building footprint layer supplied by the City of Kitchener, created a subset of building footrprints over 2000 sq ft. Then visually compared this subset with those in Bldg_Lg layer. Footprints that were new/or had addtions were appended to the Bldg_Lg dataset. The subset of RMW_pt was also used to identify those buildings which should be added.

Using the 2006 10cm imagery , RMW_pt, and the non-residential building permits (BP_ICI) identified building footprints in Cambridge and Waterloo that needed to be updated because of structural addtions or new construction.
